e and respect between spouses and the power asymmetries that structure encounters between shamans and spirits, hunters and game animals, or owners and pets, what emerges is a strong sense that the lived experience of togetherness lies at the heart of the human condition. Recognizing this relational quality of existence enables us to see how acting effectively in the world may be less a matter of individual self-assertion than learning how to elicit empathetic acts of care and attentiveness by endearing oneself to others.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aUrarina IndiansxPsychology. 0aUrarina IndiansxSocial life and customs. 0aUrarina IndiansxSocial networks. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aamazonian culture.  aamazonian history.  aamazonian studies.  aanthropology.  aarchaeology.  abiodiversity.  acultural science.  adifferent cultures.  adistractions for kids.  aeasy to read.  aengaging.  aethnography.  ahome school history books.  ahome school science books.  ahuman society.  alearning while reading.  alife in south america.  anonfiction books.  apolitics.  apsychology.  asocial science.  asouth american culture.  asouth american history.  asouth american philosophies.  asouth american politics.  aurarina.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052027359740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095421240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520954212423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520954212/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY